INSERT INTO main.reviews (id, title, platform_id, game_id, created_at, views, video, introduction, content, conclusion, positive, negative, url) VALUES (1633, 'Great (If you never played the original before)', 37, 6898, '2016-03-19 02:00:33.457000', 183, 'None', 'Pokemon Alpha Sapphire is a remake of Pokemon Sapphire for GameBoy Advanced. Like the original, you play with Brendam or May, fight against Aqua Team and Elite 4, but the game give a new sub-plot called Delta Episode, about a girl called Zina trying to stop a catastrophe to happen in Hoenn.', 'Ok, the game is exactly how was the original, but with better graphics and music, and that is the problem I had with the game. The other remakes give something more to the original, a thing that AS can''t do. FRLG give a pos-game and a better mechanic and HGSS upgraded the plot and give a better mechanic. (Yey, pokemon can follow you). First, the main plot, is the same thing as the original, but I kind had issues with the caves because for some reason they shrink in this remake. And the best point of the game is the Delta Episode, but he is very short. After we beat the E4 and do the Delta Episode you can fight in the Battle Maison or go in the internet and fight against strangers or friends. I still miss the Battle Frontier in this one and ,odd enough, you can''t fight against the leaders again. Also they didn''t upgrade the berry trees, it was tiring taking care of the trees in the originals and didn''t change in the remake. They could make this a mini-game or something. To end, I love the music. If you loved the RSE soundtrack, you will love this one.', 'It''s a average game if you played the original before and expected "Hoenn and something more", but If you never played the original you will probably love.', ' Great Soundtrack
INSERT INTO main.reviews (id, title, platform_id, game_id, created_at, views, video, introduction, content, conclusion, positive, negative, url) VALUES (1634, 'A Great RPG for sure.', 6, 76, '2016-03-19 02:51:55.257999', 225, 'None', 'For start the game give you the possibility to play 3 races (Human, Elf or Dwarf) and 3 classes (Warrior, Rogue and Mage), and each one of this choices can change some aspects in the game, as the most prominent is the prologue, with 6 different origins for the main character. You found companions (10 people, only 1 or 2 is mandatory) that can help you with the task to save the continent of Thedas of a great evil.', 'The game really has a tree of events based in your choices and origins, that make each replay you do unique. The gameplay also offered a lot way of play the game, with a varied of skills to use and you trully need a little strategy if you will play in high levels. Despite of this some people maybe don''t like of the gameplay, some say that the game maybe didn''t age very well in this part, but for me the gameplay is normal (Maybe I''m just old school), so if you wonder about play this game or not It''s good think about this. Also the game is very rpg-like, in other words, you are the main character, this maybe is not important, but I see a lot people complaining about the lack of personality of the main character about this feature, so it always depends of your taste. The lore is awesome and made you want to know more about the universe of Dragon Age, it''s so true that the story expanded to books and comics. Graphics are average, even for that time, and just to say I found the poker face that the main character does every time in the game very creepy. The soundtrack made by Inon Zur is fantastic.', 'A great RPG with a great story and soundtrack. Maybe the gameplay and graphic are outdate, but I think everyone should give at least one try in this wonderful game.', ' Soundtrack
